title: High school roundup: JC cliches STAC Central division
text:
High school roundup: JC cliches STAC Central division 
By wbng sports October 7, 2015 Updated Oct 7, 2015 at 11:56 PM EDT 
Johnson City, NY (WBNG Binghamton) Haris Brkovic scored two goals in the first 11 minutes as Johnson City rolled past Seton, 8-0, to clinch the STAC Central division in boy's soccer. 
Brkovic scored four goals in all to lead the way for the Wildcats. 
By clinching the STAC Central, JC earns a spot in the STAC semifinals on Oct. 17. 
Owego 5 - Susquehanna Valley 3 Owego got a pair of goals from Ethan Pryor as the Indians beat Susquehanna Valley, 5-3, in boy's soccer on Wednesday. 
Whitney Point field hockey edges Vestal Whitney Point scored with less than four minutes remaining to beat Vestal, 2-1, in field hockey on Wednesday night. 
It was a game that put the defending Class C state champions against the Class B state semifinalists from a year ago. 
The Eagles, the defending state champs, move to 10-3 on the season with the win.
